About Us
THE FORGOTTEN COAST'S NEWEST RV RETREAT
Steps away from the sugar white sand beach, immerse yourself in tranquility at Coastal Soul RV Beach Retreat. Located in sunny Port Saint Joe along the Indian Pass, this private RV site makes for the perfect destination that is your next vacation getaway. Catering to all RVers of discerning taste.
﻿

THE SITE
Our private, oversized site was designed for our Motor Coach with a convenient pull-in. It offers peace & quiet to all
RVers
, as it is nestled among a handful of vacation homes but still 300 ft from the sugary sands of the secluded beach and down the street from the beautiful bay.
Our  layout is designed as a Pull-In Site for Motorcoaches.
Hook-ups are on the left side.
If you are in a 5th Wheel/Travel Trailer, you may need extra sewage hose, water line, and electric.
This generous size allows for your motor coach to spread out while leaving ample room for your favorite activities. It is also equipped with
full hook-ups, wifi
, sunning deck with chaise loungers, umbrella, outdoor shower, weekly trash service and a fire pit ready for late-night s'mores, stargazing, and ghost stories.
THE FOUR-LEGGED PERK
We know you love your four-legged family members, and Coastal Soul does too. All dogs are welcome! The dog-friendly beach is Fido's dream location to catch a frisbee and snooze in the sun.

THE BEACH
Spend your vacation exploring the waters of the forgotten coast without the crowds of tourists. The shoreline is steps away from Coastal Soul and as it faces west it delivers spectacular sunsets.
Hunt for sand dollars, take a peaceful stroll along the dunes or enjoy an old fashion beach bonfire at midnight while searching for the milky way.
Bring your fishing poles, because world-class fishermen boast their biggest catches in this secret spot. Located near the Indian Pass Boat Ramp, you'll enjoy easy access to Saint Vincent Sound and the Gulf of Mexico. Don't forget your paddle boards and kayaks, too- it's the nature enthusiast's dream!
THE BAY
Some people swear walking into the clear saltwater is like wading into your own private aquarium. Sound intriguing? St. Joseph Bay is filled with turtles, dolphin, fish, seahorses and more. With her soft, grass flats and clear shallow water, she is a kayaker’s and snorkeler’s dream. Even in the deeper water, the current is calm and perfect for paddleboarding or an eco tour. Have a few adventures you’d like to check off your list? Come be wowed by trees, wildlife and our beautiful Bay.

THE TOWN
Reminiscent of Old Florida, downtown Port Saint Joe is a 20-minute cruise up the road. Find local farmers' markets, antique shops, and fresh seafood and live entertainment at the World Famous Indian Pass Raw Bar.
